1 B. The dismissal and suspension provisions of the Teacher Due
2 Process Act of 1990 shall apply to teachers who are employed on
3 temporary contracts for a complete school year and to teachers who
4 are employed in positions fully funded by federal or private
5 categorical grants, except that such teachers shall be employed only
6 for the duration of the temporary contract or the grant.
7 C. The evaluation provisions in Sections 6-101.10 and 6-101.11
8 of this title and in the Teacher Due Process Act of 1990 shall apply
9 to teachers who are employed on temporary contracts for a complete
10 school year and to teachers who are employed in positions fully
11 funded by federal or private categorical grants, except that such
12 teachers shall be employed only for the duration of the temporary
13 contract or the grant.
14 D. Teachers other than those specifically excepted in
15 subsection A of this section who are employed on contracts shall be
16 afforded all substantive and procedural rights set forth in the
17 Teacher Due Process Act of 1990 including the dismissal, suspension,
18 and nonreemployment provisions applicable to probationary or career
19 teachers as defined in Section 6-101.3 of this title.
20 E. On and after the effective date of this act July 1, 1999,
21 any teacher who has worked a complete school year under a temporary
22 contract in a school district shall be granted a year of service
23 credit toward career status in that district.
24
