1 F. No teacher shall be hired on a temporary contract by a
2 school district for more than four semesters or on multiple
3 temporary contracts by a school district that together are for more
4 than four semesters, except for a:
5 1. Teacher hired to replace a teacher who is on an approved
6 leave of absence and who is expected to return to employment with
7 the school district; or
8 2. Teacher who is a retired member of the Teachers' Retirement
9 System of Oklahoma; or
10 3. Teacher who is employed by a school district on an emergency
11 or provisional certificate.
12 G. No teacher shall be offered a temporary contract with a
13 school district without a full written disclosure at the time a
14 position is offered by the administration of the school district
15 which sets forth the terms and conditions of the temporary contract.
16 In the event the school district fails to provide such written
17 disclosure, the teacher shall be considered as employed on a
18 continuing contract basis.
19 H. On and after the effective date of this act July 1, 1999, no
20 teacher who is employed on a continuing contract basis by a school
21 district shall be reemployed on a temporary contract in that school
22 district.
23 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
